        <iri>
          <value>https://w3id.org/italia/onto/OpenCUP/Acquisto_di_beni</value>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/onto/OpenCUP/Acquisto_di_beni</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Acquisto di beni</lexicalForm>
                <datatype>None</datatype>
                <language>it</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/onto/OpenCUP/Acquisto_di_beni</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Purchase of goods</lexicalForm>
                <datatype>None</datatype>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/onto/OpenCUP/Acquisto_di_beni</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Progetto di investimento pubblico di un ente pubblico per l’acquisto di beni «durevoli» (macchinari di un ospedale, sedi o arredi per uffici amministrativi) con il pagamento, da parte dell’ente medesimo, dei costi richiesti dal venditore; il CUP è richiesto dall’ente titolare del progetto. (Delibera CIPE n. 63/2020).</lexicalForm>
                <datatype>None</datatype>
                <language>it</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://w3id.org/italia/onto/OpenCUP/Acquisto_di_beni</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>A public investment project by a public entity for the purchase of "durable" goods (hospital equipment, offices, or furniture for administrative offices), with the entity itself paying the costs requested by the seller; the CUP is requested by the entity owning the project. (CIPE Resolution No. 63/2020).</lexicalForm>
                <datatype>None</datatype>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
        </iri>
